    "Id": "vehicledef_PATTON",
    "Name": "Patton Tank",
    "UIName": "Patton Tank (Standard)",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Patton Tank</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Standard </color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>4/6 (Tracked)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>260 Fusion</color></b>\n\nThe Patton is a 65-ton armored combat vehicle specialized in conventional warfare. It is identical to the Rommel tank in all but armament and armor configuration.\n\nUnlike the Rommel, which features a massive and powerful AC/20 as its main gun, the Patton mounts an AC/10, giving it twice the ammunition capacity and superior firing range. This also enables the Patton to be fitted with more armor. The Patton also carries an LRM-5 for added punch at range, and a turret-mounted Small Laser and a Flamer to deal with attacking infantry.",
